    {
      "id": 6678,
      "name": "OpenShift Storage",
      "description": "Storage header",
      "type": "text",
      "theme": "newSolidGray",
      "interval": 5,
      "timescale": "day",
      "displaySettings": {},
      "content": "<h2>OpenShift Storage</h2><p>Consolidated view of persistent storage layers: OpenShift Data Foundation (Ceph block + file + RGW, plus NooBaa S3 gateway) and Portworx. Designed for storage admins watching fleet capacity, degraded placement groups, OSD/node availability, and commit latency.</p><p><strong>Sections:</strong> Ceph cluster health &middot; Placement groups &amp; NooBaa &middot; OSDs &amp; Ceph monitors &middot; Portworx cluster &middot; KVDB &amp; Autopilot &middot; Capacity gauges &middot; Active storage alerts</p><p><strong>Source:</strong> PromQL queries via Thanos Querier on each cluster. Devices auto-bind via categories <code>OpenShift_ODF</code> and <code>OpenShift_Portworx</code>.</p>"
    },
